info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 19 at 11:58AM PST until November 21 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST TUESDAY... * WHAT...North winds 30 to 45 mph with gusts of 60 mph becoming northeast tonight through Tuesday morning. Local gusts to 80 mph in the western San Gabriel mountains. * WHERE...Southern Ventura County Mountains, Interstate 5 Corridor and Western San Gabriel Mountains and Highway 14 Corridor. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as trees and power lines. Power outages are likely. Travel will be difficult, especially for drivers of high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
